We designed a tilting cup to encourage people to drink more water. Simple reminders like alarms are often ignored, but people are more likely to react when they see an object tipping over. This inspired our design: a cup that appears to be tilting. When users reach out to steady it, they naturally pick up the cup and drink, promoting the habit of staying hydrated.

Polysurface Texture! Check out how Joseph Lee from our Ad. Parametric Texture Workshop created this texture concept of the Bosch IXO 3 for his final project at Cademy! Joseph modeled the base surface in Rhino, using Kangaroo simulation to distribute particles across the surface or polysurface. These particles were then used to construct planes normal to the surface. He also created a circular pattern on the surface and designed a cross-section to use with a rail revolve. The cross-section smoothly transitions with curvature continuity along the rail.
